    <node id="ins_camera">
      <data key="d0">ins_camera</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">**Summary of ins_camera:**  

ins_camera is a namespace or organizational entity primarily associated with camera technology, particularly focusing on resolution standards, settings, and configurations. It contains definitions, enumerations, and specifications related to camera functionality, including resolution modes, exposure settings, and other camera-related parameters. The namespace appears to be part of a software development kit (SDK) or a broader photography technology framework, likely used for defining and managing camera operations in software applications. While descriptions vary slightly—some emphasizing its role as a namespace and others suggesting it may also represent an organization—the consistent theme is its involvement in camera resolution and settings management.  

In summary, ins_camera serves as a structured repository for camera-related technical specifications, whether as part of a software library, SDK, or a broader camera technology initiative. Its primary purpose is to standardize and provide accessible definitions for camera resolutions, exposure modes, and other configurable parameters in digital imaging systems.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-c75801d27b82e9594a84d50ad0597a7d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2711c2ea42c15a5c9f49caeb222ae1ae&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-26e050873d91d2bf23832d60f9d258b9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d69db9038c09ba66ce88754af0a8912d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93897da2927f068994bb4f709fa21c03&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-384c57a58d05d3500b8796425a332364&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-75e8827d7e52b6efb568612785a15d19&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0d93d0b1f59ae5cbb761dfac96563859</data>
      <data key="d4">photography__settings_8h.tex&lt;SEP&gt;namespaces.tex</data>
