      <data key="d3">chunk-cf528e8c49e57139843f81256f635dc7</data>
      <data key="d4">README.md</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Pro Camera API">
      <data key="d0">Pro Camera API</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">Pro Camera API provides a way to execute commands asynchronously, particularly for time-consuming tasks like 'take_picture' and 'stop_record'.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-90835cefa1becc69847978b62c9a10af</data>
      <data key="d4">async_command_handling.md</data>
    </node>
    <node id="take_picture">
      <data key="d0">take_picture</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">A command used in the Pro Camera API for capturing images, executed asynchronously with a sequence identifier for result retrieval.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-90835cefa1becc69847978b62c9a10af</data>
      <data key="d4">async_command_handling.md</data>
    </node>
    <node id="stop_record">
      <data key="d0">stop_record</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">A command used in the Pro Camera API for stopping recordings, executed asynchronously with a sequence identifier for result retrieval.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-90835cefa1becc69847978b62c9a10af</data>
      <data key="d4">async_command_handling.md</data>
    </node>
    <node id="get_result">
      <data key="d0">get_result</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">A command in the Pro Camera API designed to retrieve the actual results of previously executed asynchronous commands using their sequence IDs.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-90835cefa1becc69847978b62c9a10af</data>
      <data key="d4">async_command_handling.md</data>
    </node>
    <node id="State polling">
      <data key="d0">State polling</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">A method introduced in the Pro Camera API to check the status of asynchronous tasks via the '_idRes' attribute in the state command response.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-90835cefa1becc69847978b62c9a10af</data>
      <data key="d4">async_command_handling.md</data>
    </node>
    <node id="state">
      <data key="d0">state</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">A command in Pro Camera API that provides system status including completed async operations through '_idRes' attribute.&lt;SEP&gt;The state indicates the completion status of the async command (e.g., 'done').&lt;SEP&gt;A field in response indicating whether the request was successfully executed (done/exception/error).</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-fb6c8a33f665a1252523a39d11f66dc3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4ebfc5a85834e7af502df36580b269e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-90835cefa1becc69847978b62c9a10af</data>
      <data key="d4">overview.md&lt;SEP&gt;async_command_handling.md&lt;SEP&gt;list_files.md</data>
    </node>
    <node id="_idRes">
      <data key="d0">_idRes</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">An attribute in state command response that lists sequence IDs of completed asynchronous operations.&lt;SEP&gt;_idRes is an array of finished async command sequences in the state response.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-90835cefa1becc69847978b62c9a10af&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-29ce2d212805bfbc1a70dc74063e9d1d</data>
      <data key="d4">state_polling.md&lt;SEP&gt;async_command_handling.md</data>
    </node>
    <node id="sequence">
      <data key="d0">sequence</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">A unique identifier returned by async commands that acts as a task token for result retrieval.&lt;SEP&gt;Sequence is an identifier used for handling asynchronous command responses.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-fb6c8a33f665a1252523a39d11f66dc3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-90835cefa1becc69847978b62c9a10af</data>
      <data key="d4">async_command_handling.md&lt;SEP&gt;list_files.md</data>
    </node>
