      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">Insta360 Pro2 is an advanced 360-degree camera with higher resolution, HDR support, and enhanced bitrate options.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-70cd8de5774da924ed7695eacebca82b</data>
      <data key="d4">capabilities.md</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Insta360 Titan">
      <data key="d0">Insta360 Titan</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">Insta360 Titan is a high-end 360-degree camera offering ultra-high resolutions and 3D output capabilities.&lt;SEP&gt;Insta360 Titan is a high-end camera model supported by the Insta360 Pro Camera API, designed for professional use.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-70cd8de5774da924ed7695eacebca82b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-30f55c23379fa246af6d173ec3cc8323</data>
      <data key="d4">capabilities.md&lt;SEP&gt;README.md</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Resolution">
      <data key="d0">Resolution</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">Resolution refers to the maximum output and single-lens capabilities of the Insta360 cameras, including support for 3D and real-time stitching.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-70cd8de5774da924ed7695eacebca82b</data>
      <data key="d4">capabilities.md</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Real-time Stitching">
      <data key="d0">Real-time Stitching</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">Real-time stitching is a feature in Insta360 cameras that allows for immediate panoramic or 3D output during recording.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-70cd8de5774da924ed7695eacebca82b</data>
      <data key="d4">capabilities.md</data>
    </node>
    <node id="3D Output">
      <data key="d0">3D Output</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">3D output is a capability of Insta360 cameras, enabling the creation of stereoscopic 360-degree content.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-70cd8de5774da924ed7695eacebca82b</data>
      <data key="d4">capabilities.md</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Single Lens Resolution">
      <data key="d0">Single Lens Resolution</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">The resolution capability of individual camera lenses, ranging from 1920x1080 to 5280x3956 across different models.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-70cd8de5774da924ed7695eacebca82b</data>
      <data key="d4">capabilities.md</data>
    </node>
