    </node>
    <node id="JSON">
      <data key="d0">JSON</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">JSON is a lightweight data-interchange format used for structuring data in requests and responses.&lt;SEP&gt;JSON is the data format used for both the request and response of the listFiles command.&lt;SEP&gt;JSON is the data format used for encoding commands and responses in the Insta360 Pro Camera API.&lt;SEP&gt;The data interchange format used for both the request parameters and response structure in the camera command API.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-6c09e9b113698f3f2c7af677d45cca36&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fb6c8a33f665a1252523a39d11f66dc3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4ebfc5a85834e7af502df36580b269e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-30f55c23379fa246af6d173ec3cc8323</data>
      <data key="d4">overview.md&lt;SEP&gt;README.md&lt;SEP&gt;get_options_cmd.md&lt;SEP&gt;list_files.md</data>
    </node>
    <node id="HTTP">
      <data key="d0">HTTP</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">HTTP is the protocol used for transferring commands and data between clients and Insta360 Pro cameras via the API.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-30f55c23379fa246af6d173ec3cc8323</data>
