    <node id="Insta360 Pro series camera">
      <data key="d0">Insta360 Pro series camera</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">The Insta360 Pro series camera is a professional-grade camera offering two live modes: 'normal' and 'origin live', with varying resolutions and stitching capabilities.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-c47ca274d028552baef243300c29e96d</data>
      <data key="d4">start_live_cmd.md</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Normal Mode">
      <data key="d0">Normal Mode</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">Normal mode pushes a single stitched equirectangular/cube mapped stream with a maximum resolution of 3840x3840 due to on-board stitching limits.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-c47ca274d028552baef243300c29e96d</data>
      <data key="d4">start_live_cmd.md</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Origin Live Mode">
      <data key="d0">Origin Live Mode</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">Origin live mode pushes multiple fisheye streams (one per lens) for out-camera stitching, supporting resolutions up to 8K or 11K for Titan, requiring client-side real-time stitching.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-c47ca274d028552baef243300c29e96d</data>
      <data key="d4">start_live_cmd.md</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Stitching">
      <data key="d0">Stitching</data>
      <data key="d1">category</data>
      <data key="d2">Stitching is a process available only in normal mode, combining multiple fisheye streams into a single equirectangular/cube mapped output.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-c47ca274d028552baef243300c29e96d</data>
      <data key="d4">start_live_cmd.md</data>
    </node>
    <node id="Titan">
      <data key="d0">Titan</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">Titan is a variant of the Insta360 Pro series camera capable of supporting 11K resolution in origin live mode.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-c47ca274d028552baef243300c29e96d</data>
      <data key="d4">start_live_cmd.md</data>
    </node>
